Philippine Stocks: Ayala Corp., Philex Mining, Semirara Mining

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-05-03T00:40:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/philippine-stocks-ayala-corp-philex-mining-semirara-mining.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.2 percent to
4,326.76.  Ayala Corp. (AC)  : The owner of the largest Philippine
developer said demand for its 10-year bond is estimated at more
than twice the 10-billion pesos ($234 million) offered at a rate
of 6.8 percent. Ayala’s bond will refinance its preferred “B”
shares and will be sold until May 6, the company said in an e-
mailed statement. The stock decreased 1.8 percent to 384 pesos.  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  : The largest Philippine metals
producer had its 12-month share price estimate increased to
26.80 pesos from 16.95 pesos at Philippine Equity Partners Inc.
The stock’s “buy” rating was maintained, according to the
Manila-based brokerage. The stock climbed 3.5 percent to 18.42
pesos.  Semirara Mining Corp. (SCC)  : Shareholders at the
nation’s largest coal producer approved the development of an
industrial park in the province of Batangas, a stock exchange
filing showed. Separately, the Philippine Star today quoted
Chief Executive Officer Isidro Consunji as saying that the
company is projecting profit of as much as 5.6 billion pesos
this year from its power generation and coal mining operations.
The stock climbed 1.4 percent to 221 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
